-- CFC Insurance of Kenya Gets Approval to Begin Trading Its Stock on Bourse
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2010-11-15T13:36:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-15/cfc-insurance-of-kenya-gets-approval-to-begin-trading-its-stock-on-bourse.html
CFC Insurance Holdings Ltd., a unit
of  CFC Stanbic Holdings , received regulatory approval to sell
shares on the Kenyan stock exchange.  It will “list by introduction” 515 million shares, the
Nairobi-based Capital Markets Authority said in an e-mailed
statement today.  CFC Insurance, which owns CFC Life Assurance Ltd. and the
Heritage Insurance Co., will start trading before the end of the
year, CFC Stanbic Managing Director,  Kitili Mbathi  said Aug. 30.  CFC Stanbic shareholders approved on Aug. 9 a plan to
delink its insurance businesses. The company also owns CFC
Stanbic Bank Ltd., the Kenyan unit of Standard Bank Group Ltd.
of South Africa, and brokerage CFC Stanbic Financial Services
Ltd.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
